<%- include('../partials/header') %>

<h1>Owner / Admin Dashboard</h1>
<p>Complete system control overview.</p>

<div class="admin-controls grid">
    
    <div class="card">
        <h2>Inventory Management</h2>
        <a href="/catalog" class="btn">Browse Inventory</a>
        <a href="/dashboard" class="btn-secondary">Back to Shared Dashboard</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>Category Management</h2>
        <a href="/catalog?category=Cars" class="btn">View Cars</a>
        <a href="/catalog?category=SUVs" class="btn-secondary">View SUVs</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>Employee Tools</h2>
        <a href="/employee/dashboard" class="btn">Access Employee View</a>
        <a href="/admin/employees" class="btn-secondary">Manage Staff Accounts</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h2>System Activity Logs</h2>
        <a href="/service-requests" class="btn">View Service Activity</a>
        <a href="/reviews" class="btn-secondary">Review Activity</a>
    </div>

</div>

<section class="card glass-panel">
    <h2>Required Data Model (Project Scope)</h2>
    <p>The platform is designed around these core tables and relationships:</p>
    <ul style="padding-left: 1.2rem;">
        <li>Users table with a role field (User, Employee, Admin).</li>
        <li>Vehicles table for core listing and pricing data.</li>
        <li>Categories table linked to vehicles.</li>
        <li>Reviews table linked to users and vehicles.</li>
        <li>Service requests table linked to users with status tracking.</li>
        <li>Contact messages table from the public form.</li>
        <li>Vehicle images table with one-to-many relationship to vehicles.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

